<title>GREECE: SIGMA, NATIONAL TOP GREEK BROKERS JUNE MARKET SHARES.</title>
<headline>SIGMA, NATIONAL TOP GREEK BROKERS JUNE MARKET SHARES.</headline>
<dateline>ATHENS 1997-07-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>June trading volume at the Athens</p>
<p>stock exchange reached 940.23 billion drachmas, down from May's</p>
<p>1.16 trillion, the exchange's members association (SMEHA) said.</p>
<p>Sigma Securities retook the lead with 9.79 percent of the</p>
<p>business followed by National Securities with 8.59 percent.</p>
<p>Alpha Brokerage which led in May fell to third place with</p>
<p>7.94 percent.</p>
<p>Telesis Securities, N. Devletoglou and Kappa Securities saw</p>
<p>their rankings unchanged from the previous month.</p>
<p>Cumulative first half trading volume surged to 4.63 trillion</p>
<p>drachmas -- an impressive improvement over 1996 when the entire</p>
<p>year's volume was 2.53 trillion drachmas.</p>
<p>SMEHA released the following data and market share rankings</p>
<p>for June. The top 15 brokers shared 64 percent of the bourse's</p>
<p>trading volume. The remainder went to the exchange's other 49</p>
<p>brokers.</p>
<p>    BROKER		     VOLUME JUNE	   MARKET SHARE</p>
<p>				   (in drs billion)</p>
<p>1.  Sigma			  92.0			9.79%</p>
<p>2.  National		     80.8			8.59%</p>
<p>3.  Alpha			  74.6			7.94%</p>
<p>4.  Telesis			70.7			7.52%</p>
<p>5.  Devletoglou		  39.4			4.20%</p>
<p>6.  Commercial		   36.7			3.91%</p>
<p>7.  Midland			34.3			3.66%</p>
<p>8.  Metrolife		    27.7			2.95%</p>
<p>9.  Ergo			   25.8			2.75%</p>
<p>10. Kappa			  25.2			2.68%</p>
<p>11. Omega			  21.4			2.28%</p>
<p>12. Interact		     20.6			2.19%</p>
<p>13. Hellenic		     20.3			2.17%</p>
<p>14. Aspis			  17.8			1.90%</p>
<p>15. Intersec		     16.6			1.77%</p>
<p>    Total volume		940.2</p>
